Unless I'm missing something, it doesn't look like there's any release corresponding to this retain in the later callbacks. Also it would in any case be better to replace this line with just `msg = null;` - no need to retain if releasing immediately after.

Something like this, though maybe with some more try/finallys: 82da56c77f90c572f0dbbfcb408c780e506d42ca
